In 1957 - Soviet Union launached Sputnik

Then US launached - ARPA (Advanced Research Project Agency)

In 1960's to 1970's -
They were not able to share information among themselves

so ARPA created a communication between their computers , so they can share information

In 1969 , ARPANET was born[so that ARPA's computers can talk to each other]

Around 1980 , they started transmitting to TCP/IP protocol
At this point of time , ARPANet called Internet

in 1990's the researcher of CERN , they similarly felt need of sharing information
they used hyperlink based documents

In 1990 - Tim BernerLee introduced World Wide Web
in which they store and retreive information

Initial browsers supporting www - Mosaic, Netscape browsers
